Edit Model Settings

You can update model settings that were previously set during model deployment.

To edit model settings:

1. View a Prediction Definition in Model Manager.
2. On the Model Settings subtab, change the settings you want.

COLUMN	DESCRIPTION
Model Name	Change the model's display name.
Model Threshold	For the classification use case, you can update the threshold value for a model.
Object Connection	If applicable, change the Salesforce object associated with this model.
Actionable Variables	If applicable, select actionable variables to trigger improvements.
Segmentation Filters	Choose whether to use the model to get predictions on all data or just a segment of the data.
title: Editing Model Settings in Salesforce Einstein Discovery
